period
Honest question from a novice/first time watching a  Coi Leray video, but isn't she Benzino's daughter? If so, then why is she rapping about "pulling up on an op and watch it Blick, Blick"? I highly doubt she grew up in the trenches and even if she did, she doesn't strike me as the type to be doing the heavy lifting. Surprisingly to me (again, first time even seeing her), she is actually fairly decent sounding and low key cute as hell. She had a couple of flow switch ups and tbh I feel she had the better of the verses between the Queen and herself (please don't kill me "Barbs"). I'm just a dumb man from no where so my opinion isn't valid but I feel as though she should stick to rapping about what she lived and her present experiences. Part of being a dope MC is being able to draw inspiration from past experiences and trauma and flipping it into amazing lyrical art. Does anyone else feel cringy listening to an 85lb girl that grew up super privileged/wealthy rapping about spinning the block and dropping ops? Maybe I'm alone on this but I guess I just only fuck with rappers that rap about their truth or at least the truth of something they've witnessed. Shit is corny to me when a trust fund baby pretends that she got it out the mud, then proceeds to get on a trap beat and twerks whilst simultaneously talking about killing ops. Do you but miss me with this.

Death, it's one of the biggest events that will ever take place in your life. We face death everyday, conscious or unconsciously of it; death lurks around every corner of our life. Like a lion waiting to catch its prey, death comes for us all in many shapes and forms; seemingly there is no one who can escape from the jaws of death.  But did you know there is a reason why we die? The idea of death you're familiar with is only the tip of the iceberg. See we die because we've sinned against God. Death according to the bible is wages " for the wages of sin is death " (Romans 6:23).  Because man sinned against God, we live in a fallen world, it was once perfect, but now in ruins. Now that sin exists, God is coming to judge the world In righteousness. "It's appointed a man once to die and after this judgement" (Hebrews 9:27) The standard he'll judge you by is the 10 commandments, God's moral law.  He's so serious about sin that he gives anyone who sins the death sentence, the bible says you've earned it through sinning against God and God pays you in death. Each time you sin you build up his wrath. â€œThe soul who sins shall die.â€ (Ezekiel 18:4) The punishment is the eternal fires of Hell " Where there will be weeping and gnashing of teeth" (Matthew 13:42)  You will have to face God on Judgement Day.   Will you go to Heaven or Hell?  Hereâ€™s a quick test:   1.You shall have no other gods before Me. (Have you always loved God above all else?)   2.You shall not make yourself an idol. (Have you made a god in your mind that you're more comfortable with, a god to suit yourself?)   3.You shall not take God's name in vain. (Have you ever used God's holy Name as a cuss word?)   4.Remember the Sabbath Day, to keep it holy.   5.Honor your father and mother.   6. You shall not murder. (God considers hatred to be as murder, 1 John 3:15).   7. You shall not commit adultery. ("Whoever looks upon a woman to lust after her has committed adultery with her already in his heart" Matthew 5:27-28; this also includes sex before marriage).   8. You shall not steal. (Have you ever stolen anything? the value of the item is irrelevant).   9. You shall not lie. (Have you lied even once? Including answering these questions).   10. You shall not covet. (Have you ever jealousy desired what belongs to others?)   James 2:10 says, â€œthe person who keeps all of the laws except one is as guilty as a person who has broken all of Godâ€™s laws.â€Â    The Bible says that God will punish all murderers, rapists, thieves, liars, adulterers, etc. He will even judge our words and thoughts.   If you have done any of those things, God sees you as guilty of breaking His law and the Bible warns that the guilty will end up in Hell. Will YOU be guilty on Judgement Day?Â    "For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord." (Romans 6:23)   God sent His Son to suffer and die on the cross. Jesus took the punishment upon Himself and defeated death on the cross; not because you're Good but because God is rich in mercy.   â€œFor God so loved the world that He gave His only Son, whoever believes in Him should not perish but have eternal life.â€ (John 3:16)   Jesus rose from the dead and defeated death. Repent (turn from sin) today and trust in Jesus and God will grant you everlasting life.   Then, Read the Bible and obey what you read.
